description.narrative: Due to COVID-19 outbreak in China, it was not possible to encourage adolescents to lead on-site activities in their communities. The focus has been adjusted to help adolescents deal with the stress and other psychosocial issues. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/07/2020

title.narrative: Life skills modules adopted by government and incorporated in vocational education curriculum

target.value: 2020:Modules adopted and included in school curriculum

actual.value: 2019:Four skills models revised and used for training of 7,374 vocational schools adolescents in 11 provinces. Evidence collected in pilots and from desk research informed dialogues with MOE on integration of skills module in vocational education curriculum.

title.narrative: Gender-sensitive life skills modules for OOS adolescents finalized and disseminated and used on multiple platforms

baseline.value: Modules not yet finalized, 0 hits on digital platforms and app

target.value: 2020:Modules package finalized and available in print and a range of digital formats; 100,000 hits on digital platforms and app

actual.value: 2019:A total of eight 21st century skills modules being tested and refined in 28 counties of 13 provinces.
